  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "There are numerous films that explore the theme of individuals discovering and harnessing hidden powers, especially when faced with intense or high-stakes situations. Here are some noteworthy examples:\n\n1. **The Matrix (1999)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Neo, a computer hacker, discovers that reality as he knows it is a simulated illusion. Under extreme circumstances, he awakens to his true potential and becomes \"The One\" capable of manipulating the Matrix.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Neo's latent abilities are unlocked when he is thrust into life-or-death situations, forcing him to realize and master his hidden powers.\n\n2. **Unbreakable (2000)**\n   - **Synopsis:** David Dunn, a security guard, discovers he has superhuman strengths after surviving a catastrophic train wreck without injury. His abilities emerge fully as he faces greater threats.\n   - **Why It Fits:** The pressure of surviving the accident acts as a catalyst for David to uncover and develop his extraordinary powers.\n\n3. **Captain America: The First Avenger (2011)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Steve Rogers, a frail young man, is transformed into the super-soldier Captain America through a secret experiment. His abilities are honed in the crucible of war.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Steve's hidden potential is unlocked and enhanced under the extreme conditions of World War II.\n\n4. **Harry Potter Series (2001\u20132011)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Harry Potter discovers he is a wizard on his 11th birthday and attends Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, where he learns to harness his magical abilities, especially when facing dark forces.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Harry's magical powers are further realized and refined as he confronts increasing threats and challenges.\n\n5. **Logan (2017)**\n   - **Synopsis:** In a dystopian future, an aging Wolverine (Logan) is forced to confront his inner powers and past as he protects a young mutant from sinister forces.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Logan taps into his regenerative abilities and combat skills in high-pressure scenarios to ensure survival and protect others.\n\n6. **Doctor Strange (2016)**\n   - **Synopsis:** After a tragic accident, Dr. Stephen Strange discovers the hidden world of magic and alternate dimensions, eventually becoming a master sorcerer.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Stephen's journey into discovering and mastering his mystical powers is accelerated by personal loss and existential threats.\n\n7. **The Incredibles (2004)**\n   - **Synopsis:** A family of superheroes must come out of retirement to save the world, each member utilizing their unique superpowers.\n   - **Why It Fits:** The family members are initially unaware or repressed of their abilities but are compelled to use them in response to looming dangers.\n\n8. **Bruce Almighty (2003)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Bruce Nolan is granted divine powers by God to understand the challenges of omnipotence, leading him to discover capabilities he never knew he had.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Bruce's hidden potential as a conduit of divine power is unleashed when he is given the responsibility to manage the world's affairs.\n\n9. **Limitless (2011)**\n   - **Synopsis:** Eddie Morra takes a mysterious drug that allows him to access 100% of his brain's potential, unlocking extraordinary cognitive abilities.\n   - **Why It Fits:** Eddie's enhanced mental powers surface as he navigates high-stakes situations in business and personal life.\n\n10. **Matilda (1996)**\n    - **Synopsis:** A young girl named Matilda discovers she has telekinetic powers, which she uses to overcome challenges posed by her family and school principal.\n    - **Why It Fits:** Matilda's latent psychic abilities emerge as she confronts oppressive environments, allowing her to assert control and justice.\n\nThese films explore the journey of characters unlocking and mastering their hidden abilities, often driven by urgent or challenging circumstances that necessitate the use of their newfound powers. Whether through self-discovery, external catalysts, or transformative events, each movie offers a unique take on the theme of latent potential realized under pressure.",
